Admin panel: full roster management (add / rename / archive / delete)

Players tab grows from a read-only list into a full management UI:
- "+ Add player" with auto-suggested ID (slugified from name, collision-safe)
- Inline rename (Enter saves, Escape cancels)
- Toggle fixed/guest in place
- Archive (soft delete) and Restore — preserves all history
- Hard delete with confirm, cascades attendance/stats/votes/claims/guests
- "Show archived" toggle to keep archived players out of the way

DB (supabase/admin_player_ops.sql, idempotent):
- New `players.archived_at` timestamptz column + partial index
- admin_archive_player / admin_restore_player
- admin_delete_player (deletes from attendance, player_stats, motm_votes,
  player_claims, then players)
- admin_add_player (validates name + id, prevents id collision)
- admin_update_player (rename + toggle fixed)

Client visibility rules for archived players:
- fixedPlayers excludes archived (drops them from attendance UI for new
  games and from "missing" counts)
- externalPlayerPool excludes archived (guest dropdown stays clean)
- allGamePlayers excludes archived UNLESS they have a row in the
  currently-selected game (past games stay accurate)
- TeamStatsPage live builder excludes archived (static snapshot
  unaffected — that's the source of truth for its season)

useFutsalData now exposes reloadAll so the AdminPanel can refresh
everything after each mutation. README updated with the new SQL file
and the Players tab capabilities.
